  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (06f7c9c 2023-03-18T00:08:48.50351195Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge build\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIf a lib/ dependency contains a remappings.txt file that contains a line:\r\n```\r\nsrc/=src/\r\n```\r\n\r\nthen imports in the current project's src/ directory that say, for example,\r\n```\r\nimport \"./SomeFile.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nend up resolving to the src/ directory of the dependency project in the lib/ directory instead of the src/ directory of the project being built.\r\n\r\nSee #4596 for more details.",
